{"type":"message","id":"586f793d","parentId":"779353dd","timestamp":"2026-02-23T18:27:15.254Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing emergency guidance**\n\nI’m crafting an emergency response. I should say, “Call emergency services immediately, using your local number (like 112 in India). If it’s safe, check responsiveness and breathing. If they aren’t breathing and you’re trained, start CPR. Don’t remove their helmet, apply firm pressure to any bleeding, and monitor until help arrives while keeping them warm.” I want to keep it general and avoid any specific internal steps. Alright, let’s finalize this!","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Emergency services must be called immediately (dial your local number for Noida/India, 112 or 108 ambulance). If safe to do so, check responsiveness and breathing; if they are unresponsive and not breathing, start CPR if you’re trained, and continue until help arrives. Do not remove any helmets, apply firm pressure to any visible bleeding, keep the person warm, and monitor their breathing and consciousness until professionals take over."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":239,"output":617,"cacheRead":9472,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10328,"cost":{"input":-239,"output":-617,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-856}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771871228339}}
