{"type":"message","id":"26be8307","parentId":"c18233cf","timestamp":"2026-02-23T18:27:22.313Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Providing emergency medical guidance**\n\nIt's crucial to respond with safe and concise steps in an emergency medical situation. I should emphasize that calling emergency services is the first priority. After that, if it's safe, I can suggest checking responsiveness and breathing, starting CPR if needed and trained, not removing a helmet, applying gauze to any bleeding wounds, and keeping the person warm until help arrives. I'll also ask what they'd like to do next.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Call emergency services now (India: dial 112 or 108 ambulance). If safe, check responsiveness and breathing; if unresponsive and not breathing, start CPR if you’re trained and continue until help arrives. Do not remove helmets, apply gentle pressure with clean cloth if there’s external bleeding, keep them warm, and monitor their condition until professionals take over. Do you want me to guide you step-by-step through first-aid actions or help you contact emergency services?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openrouter/auto","usage":{"input":308,"output":495,"cacheRead":9600,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":10403,"cost":{"input":-308,"output":-495,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":-803}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1771871235409}}
